content.description: Low down start with large moves up to the crack line. Holds are somewhat sparse, but a good line overall.
content.location: Left of the show of hands boulder.

content.description: Not the best rock, but it might be a good alternative warm up for the area.
content.protection: 1 pad. Maybe another to fill in the hole the rocks.
content.location: On the south side of the Show of Hands boulder. Base for starting is on a boulder.

content.description: Sit start far right arete on underwhelmed boulder.
content.location: Underwhelmed  older far right arete.

content.description: Start on undercling move up edges to sharp bulb good top out.
content.location: Two routes right of underwhelmed start. Undercling on an area.

content.description: Beginning feet are almost non-existent. Start matched on the obvious rail, move to a crimp that then utilizes better feet. Keep pulling on crimps to the horn at the top.
content.location: Around the right corner from The Fridge (v4)

content.description: sit start at the bottom of the roof. work your way under the roof until you can grab the first good hold on the face. this is where the crux begins. left toe hook under the roof and throw out to the arete. work your way up the arete and top out.
content.protection: a few boulder pads will do but its not that bad a of fall
content.location: pretty much the last boulder in the south end. you can't miss it

content.description: Start low on "Underwhelmed" but pull out onto the face using the chicken head. Bump left hand up through slopers to a blocky crimp, move right hand to small crimp on seam. At this point either dyno for the flat lip, or do a hard gaston bump with right hand up to lip.
content.location: Same boulder as underwhelmed

content.description:
I brushed and sent this route while my wife was working Underwhelmed. It could be a nice warm-up or something to occupy your weak boyfriend while you go girl-power on the harder climb next door.

Start as low as possible on the super thin "tortilla chip" edge. Traverse up the sharp edge using heel hooks until you round the corner and grab the black jugs. At this point, it's possible to release the right heel hook and catch a left toe to top out.
content.protection: A pad or two to cover some rocks.
content.location: Just east of the classic "Underwhelmed." The route starts low, traversing a thin edge to top out.

content.description:
Didn't see this one on here, so thought I'd add it.

Begin sitting just left of Loose Cannon sitting with a left hand small pocket and right hand crimp. Throw up and right to a good hold, then bump right again to a high crimp. Fire for the top. Very fun!
content.location: Left of Loose Cannon, start sitting.

content.description: Really cool features to start, but funky finish on broken and soon to break patina edges over a yuck landing. Worth a second star for the cool moves at the start, but that's maybe a bit generous. Just skip this one, eh?
content.location: In a dark cave with a funky landing. Undercling the brontosaurus penis and work up left.

content.description: Sit start on left side of Boulder good edges traversing right on good holds. Top out as far right as you can.
content.location: Boulder just south west of Dustbowl. Climb south side of the boulder.

content.description: The book has this listed as V2, but I've seen plenty of people struggle with it. Small crimps lead straight up the mini-bulge line. Trust your feet.
content.location: Around the right side of the fridge boulder.

content.description: start on triangle shaped hold at very back of cave and climb into the start of show of hands
content.location: chalked holds lower the show of hands start

content.description: I was surprised not to see this one so I figured id submit it! A classic of the area, cool holds, fun thuggy moves. Whats not to like. Sit start matched on a decent undercling edge in the back of the overhang, and throw to the two obvious incuts behind you, then slap to the lip and do a slightly awkward top out.
content.location: Really easy to find, when you're in the wash headed toward the underwhelmed/ loose cannon area this boulder is looking you right in the face on the left. Cant miss it.

content.description: Hard sit start in slopes pockets leads to a big move  and crimps. Top is a bit sandy a spotter is recommended.
content.location: Just left of settlers of Catan v11. The bolder is the first large obvious bolder as you walk into south end. Routes are on south east side

content.description: Start low on two crimps and make a hard deadpoint to a pocket. Pop out left to the rail and work your way up and left to the top.
content.location: One of the first boulders encountered in the South End. You will see a large boulder on your left with no chalk. Walk to the backside of this and Settlers is the obvious chalked line that goes left. A project is being attempted to the right.

content.description:
Great movement, good stone. This is a highlight of the area. Start low and right in the semi-slick pocket, and power up and left to bad holds, then work feet, and move to good ones. From there, climb through a series of cool sloper rail holds and up through patina crimps to the finish.

Really fun problem, a bit powerful.
content.location: This is the sit start to Chicken Soup, which is the v4 to the right of Dustbowl on the same boulder.

content.description: Same start as Rona Free. Match hands on the 1 foot wide horizontal rail. Throw up the right heal, then head up the arete.
content.protection: 1-2 pads. One to the right of the arete is helpful for the top out.
content.location: 20 yards south of the Underwhelmed boulder.

content.description: Sit start, matched on a 1 foot wide horizontal rail. Toss the right heal up and head left on nice black patina crimps and then straight up.
content.location: Located about 20 yards south of the Underwhelmed boulder.

content.description: Sit start on mega vertical jug, move left and traverse rail to the point where you can move to the single crimp in the middle of the face(about 4ish feet above the rail), move to lip and top out.
content.protection: Crash pad. Be aware of the boulder behind the problem. It shouldn't be much of a problem but anything can happen.

content.description:
Fun little boulder!

Start sitting, fire up to a right hand rounded hold with a sharp patina edge, then into a sidepull/crimp, and fire to the lip. Finish with a straight mantel. High value for a short boulder, and worth doing a couple of times.
content.location: Right of Hollywood Hazmat/Whelmed, right of the little rock sitting in front of the face, sit start on good holds

content.description:
Traversing problem on good rock with a distinct crux towards the end.

Start mostly matched on a slightly sloped crimp rail near the right arete and ride the sloper rail left to the crimpy part. A gaston move or two will get you through the crux and onto some incut jugs, then up to the next ledge and top out.

Broke part of one of the crux crimps off - if the rest of it says farewell, the grade may increase slightly. Luckily the rest of the problem is on good rock and avoids the more questionable sections.
content.protection: Three pads work well, the middle is where the spice is.
content.location:
On the north end of the area, but south of Settlers of Catan.

Start heading for Settlers of Catan from the main area, but take a right just before crossing the open area and follow the rock-lined path to the start of the problem.

content.description: Good warmup near Thundergun. Start with both hands on the flake behind the thundergun start Great feet the whole way through. Crux is the brief movement through crimps before the jugs. Topout around the side using the beautiful handle.
content.location: Right next to Thundergun Express.

content.description:
Really cool climbing in super fun pockets. Worth doing for sure.

Start lower than is described in Dallas' guide, sitting with hands matched in the pocket, and right foot presses on right side of the larger pocket around the pocket. Fire up to rad sloper, and then two finger, and then into the jug left hand pocket pinch and up to a straight mantel with face pressed against rock.

> There is also a stand start (v3? listed as v4 in the guide), with left hand in the jug pocket, and right hand on a sloper edge.

> There is also a variation on the left (v1/2?), which starts with right hand in the jug pocket, and rock up onto feet over there to the mantel.
content.protection: 2-3 pads is nice for this uneven landing, but you could sketch it out over one maybe.
content.location: Find the Settlers boulders, a unique, tall wall characterized by high friction pockets that are, admittedly, a little crossly crumbly.

content.description: This problem is surprisingly fun and not nearly as "dabby" as it appears. This problem is very much at home in Moe's, the land of lowballs!   Anyway....start matched on the obvious low flake feature, heel hook to the right. Head up to the crimp flake that looks like it will rip off, but in fact feels pretty solid. Take it to the top. A harder version could be constructed by heading right for the exit.
content.location: This boulder is 5 feet from the Loose Cannon Boulder to the west. Get down in the hole and climb out.

content.description: Fun movement on decent holds. Start low and right, sitting, on crimps. Work up to the cool pinch, and power up and left to a cool side pull, then do a tomahawk throw with right hand to the good sloper on top.
content.location: The low ochre face between Dustbowl and Show of Hands, about 8-10 feet tall.

content.description: Same start as for Underwhelmed.   Head out the backside climbing a nearly horizontal roof to reach the lip.   Heel hook and reach for some pockets to top out.   Like most of Moe's, it seems like some of these holds won't be here forever.
content.location: Under the Underwhelmed boulder.

content.description: Good pumpy route on nice edges and a cool finish move
content.location: Linkup from the start of Loose Cannon down low and right all the way into the last move of Tight Cannon.

content.description: This is a really fun, compression V4. Sit start in front of "the fridge" with a hand on both sides. Slap your way up until it's possible to grab the crimp high on the face. Top out to the left.
content.protection: A few pads and spotter. Pretty safe landing.
content.location: The Fridge is a little east of Steamfunk. It faces northwest and gets nice morning shade.

content.description: Start on Inertia, v2, and head right, finishing on the big holds left of arete + arete holds to a fun topout. Nice line, in a big spread of cool holds on the right side of the Underwhelmed boulder.
content.location: Just right of a little boulder sitting in front of the face, right of Underwhelmed, right of Hollywood Hazmat, start on Inertia, v2.

content.description:
Sit start on underclings. Work up and left through cool sculpted pinches (crux) and into resistive climbing on small chicken heads and side-pulls. Finish on an easy mantle top out.

There’s a lot of small crimps scattered throughout the cave with potential for other beta/variations.

While cleaning the boulder, I discovered several bats sleeping in a deep slot. It’s not really in the climbing path and there’s better holds all around it, but it’s good to be aware of and kind to our animal neighbors.
content.protection: A couple of pads. The climb is long and traverses a bit.
content.location: Located on the backside of the largest boulder directly uphill from Settlers of Catan, hidden in a cave created by several other large boulders.

content.description: Sit start small crimps with bad feet or campus through crimps to top.
content.location: North East side of Dustbowl bolder

content.description: Very Hueco Tanks like boulder problem. Start on the little mini arete (the starting holds are like to pinches) and work up the slopers into the slot and then to the giant flake. Then top out.
content.protection: Crash Pads. Spotters arent really needed since its sort of a low roof problem.
content.location: as you are walking south in the valley it is after settlers of catan and before show of hands and underwhelmed. the boulder is kind of long. this problem is on the south end of the boulder.

content.description: Sit start with a sloping right hand and a very low left hand undercling. Compress through fun slopers to an easy topout. First span is big and might require alternate beta for shorter climbers. Reminiscent of Yo-yo Boy/Girl.
content.location: Uphill and looker’s right from the Catan boulder. Approach using one of the small washes to minimize damage to the fragile crypto soil.

content.description: From a crimp, up to fun slopers, to a big reach to iron patina crimps. The sloper rails are fun.
content.location: On the dustbowl boulder. Start seated on crimps, shoot up to the sloper rails, and then to the crimps high up above and top out.

content.description: Start far out right, dont go up too high at the beginning, and head left. Traversing the beginning section is has some reachy moves to hit good pockets.
Bailout climb for the cartographer (v2). Just work the jugs in the center and topout before the peak.
content.location: Cartographer boulder.

content.description: Start seated and make a couple tough moves to a good hold. Lean left up the rail and top out on jugs.
content.location: Slightly left of Tight Cannon

content.description: Cool climbing on nice edges and fun balancy positions.
content.location: On the backside of the Show of Hands boulder. Start low on the obvious large block, climb up the scooped slab over the stepped landing.
